---
title: Home
permalink: /
description: I'm an active open source developer pretending to know what he's doing and in turn, always breaks the build.
---

{% extends '_layouts/base.html.twig' %}

{% from '_macros/calendar.html.twig' import calendar %}

{% set pageWideCSS = 's-homepage u-background-white' %}

{% block body %}
    <div class="c-split-container row no-gutters picture-row">
        <div class="col-lg-6 u-background-light py-5">
            <div class="c-split-container__left px-5 h5">
                {% include '_includes/navigation.html.twig' %}
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-lg-6 u-background-dark py-5">
            <div class="c-split-container__right text-center text-lg-left">
                <div class="c-thumbnail">
                    <img
                        src="https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/{{ site.author.email | md5 }}?s=200"
                        alt="allejo's profile picture"
                    >
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="u-background-white py-5 text-center">
        <h1>allejo</h1>
        <p>
            {{ site.motto }}
        </p>

        <div class="h3 m-0">
            {% include '_includes/social-media.html.twig' %}
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="c-split-container row no-gutters">
        <div class="col-lg-6 u-background-dark">
            <article class="c-split-container__left p-5">
                {% set latest_article = collections.posts | order('date', 'DESC') | first %}

                <div class="latest-post mb-4">
                    <h3 class="post-title">
                        <a href="{{ url(latest_article) }}">
                            {{ latest_article.title }}
                        </a>
                    </h3>

                    <div class="post-date">
                        {{ calendar(latest_article.date) }}
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="s-markdown mb-4">
                    {{ latest_article.content | summary }}
                </div>

                <footer class="text-right">
                    <a href="{{ url(latest_article) }}" class="c-button">
                        <i class="fa fa-fw fa-glasses" aria-hidden="true"></i>
                        Read full post
                    </a>
                </footer>
            </article>
        </div>

        <div class="col-lg-6 u-background-light">
            <div class="c-split-container__right p-5">
                <h2 class="mb-4">Want to support what I do?</h2>

                <p class="mb-4">
                    Everything I do is out of sheer unbearable boredom where I'd go crazy if I didn't keep myself occupied. In turn, you get to benefit from the random things I build. So if you want to support me, here's a few ways how.
                </p>

                <div>
                    <a href="https://buymeacoffee.com/{{ site.social.coffee.username }}" class="c-button">
                        <i class="fa fa-fw fa-coffee" aria-hidden="true"></i>
                        Buy me a coffee
                    </a>
                    <a href="https://ko-fi.com/{{ site.social.kofi.username }}" class="c-button">
                        <i class="fas fa-fw fa-utensils" aria-hidden="true"></i>
                        Feed my sushi addiction
                    </a>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <footer class="u-background-white text-center py-5">
        <span>copyright &copy; {{ 'now' | date('Y') }}</span>
    </footer>
{% endblock %}
